Here's a minimal API endpoint that accepts multiple images plus a description via `multipart/form-data`:

```csharp
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Http.Features;

var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);

// Raise the max request body size to 50 MB
builder.WebHost.ConfigureKestrel(o =>
    o.Limits.MaxRequestBodySize = 50 * 1024 * 1024);

var app = builder.Build();

app.MapPost("/upload", async (IFormFileCollection files, HttpRequest req) =>
{
    // Read the text field from the same form
    var description = req.Form["description"].ToString();

    if (files.Count == 0)
        return Results.BadRequest("No files uploaded.");

    var saved = new List<string>();

    foreach (var file in files)
    {
        // Validate content type
        if (!file.ContentType.StartsWith("image/"))
            return Results.BadRequest($"'{file.FileName}' is not an image.");

        var path = Path.Combine("uploads", file.FileName);
        Directory.CreateDirectory("uploads");

        await using var stream = File.Create(path);
        await file.CopyToAsync(stream);
        saved.Add(file.FileName);
    }

    return Results.Ok(new { description, uploadedFiles = saved });
})
.DisableAntiforgery()                 // required for form posts without a token
.Accepts<IFormFile>("multipart/form-data");

app.Run();
```

**Key points:**

- **`IFormFileCollection`** binds all files from the form; the text field is read from `req.Form["description"]`.
- **Kestrel's `MaxRequestBodySize`** defaults to ~28 MB, so bump it to 50 MB explicitly.
- **`.DisableAntiforgery()`** is needed in .NET 8+ because antiforgery is on by default for form endpoints.
- If you're behind IIS/IIS Express, also set the limit in `web.config`:

```xml
<system.webServer>
  <security>
    <requestFiltering>
      <requestLimits maxAllowedContentLength="52428800" />
    </requestFiltering>
  </security>
</system.webServer>
```

**Test with `curl`:**

```bash
curl -F "files=@photo1.jpg" \
     -F "files=@photo2.png" \
     -F "description=Vacation pics" \
     http://localhost:5000/upload
```
